<br>
I'd like to clarify something.<br>
<br>
Basically, we felt that given the sparcity of reservations, that a reservation should represent at least 18 people.  Under the old system, a guild with 7 people could make a reservation and invite 25 guests -- unguilded, a few from a lot of guilds, or whatever.<br>
<br>
Under the new system, a guild with less than 18 people can still go to the planes.  However, they will need to ally with one or more other guilds.<br>
<br>
Horizons has been doing this all along.  Our planar raids have been scheduled with Sigils and Trade Foundation.  Note that between the three guilds, not every guild is sending 7 or more people, but we consider them joint raids regardless.  In the past, Horizons did the actual bookings, but neither Sigils nor Trade Foundation scheduled any raids of their own.<br>
<br>
The reality is -- you're not going to the planes with 5 or 10 people -- you're already allying with other people to make your raids a success.  By changing the requirements, you will now need to formalize these arrangements.<br>
<br>
While this does increase the difficulty of scheduling your raids, I happen to feel it's fair.<br>
<br>
If anyone wishes to discuss this with me, feel free to contact me.  I don't recommend you try me in game -- I played a lot this weekend, but probably won't be on for the next few days.  Feel free to respond here or email me: admin@innoruuk.com.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhiraghm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hiraghm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#778899>(10/29/01 12:51:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.com/jdwilliams2/data/Aldrinshroom1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summit Clarification: Small Guilds</span><hr size=1> How does this work? How do two small guilds reserve a booking for a plane? Or does one guild reserve it and the other go as a guest?<br>
Why is there a member attendance requirement at all? If RR wishes to reserve a booking, or TD, or XYZZY, why not let them? If they can't assemble a large enough force, then their slot can revert to FFA/FiF.<br>
But gee, that might waste a reserved booking period for another, bigger guild that could use the time to get their members phat lewts.<br>
<br>
Aldrin Moonwalker<br>
