</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/urumenia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rumenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#778899>(10/29/01 12:21:36 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thevigilant.net/images/skybye.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summit Clarification: Small Guilds</span><hr size=1> What was funny about the old 'double booking' rumors was that no one ever proved it was happening. But we'll go ahead and screw over the little guy once again so that uber and zerg get a bigger piece of the pie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#778899>(10/29/01 12:43:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summit Clarification: Small Guilds</span><hr size=1> We just had a Summit, not sure why if some people have &quot;all&quot; the answers why this is even coming up.  The problem with the Guilds who don't need Planes armor only booking Epics is that lessens the chance that the smaller Guilds can do their Epics.  I have my Epic drops from Hate and Fear.  But if those MOB's were &quot;reserved&quot; for the big Guilds, now you've taken away the chances for other people in my Guild to get them.  Because you can bet damn sure if the only bookings the big Guilds got were for the Epic MOB's, they would kill them as soon as they spawn, and I wouldn't blame them.  I just see this is causing more grief then it avoids.<br>
<br>
And Rumenia, please.  For a while you were getting along with people.  Now it's back to the &quot;I hate you because you're big&quot;.  My Guild has enough to break-in to the Planes, but only if we have high turn-out.  So are we a big enough Guild to hate us? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugregar1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gregar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#778899>(10/29/01 2:37:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Summit Clarification: Small Guilds</span><hr size=1> Actually, the numbers changed, Aldrin, but the way it works is the same.  Both guilds use a booking each for the same raid.<br>
<br>
I'm wondering about the logistics nightmare of keeping track of who currently needs what epic piece from what plane at what time?  <br>
<br>
And, I guess we're the weirdos.  Our epic loot rules are the same as regular loot rules.  If you are on the raid, and you need it, you random with everyone else who can.  We don't do set-asides.  Oddly, many of our guests talk it over privately.  I'm reminded of three rogues in Hate with us who decided amongst themselves who was most &quot;needy&quot;.  The other two passed on the random.  In our eyes, that makes all three people more &quot;epic&quot; than some twinkling doodad VI cooked up.  THAT is &quot;uber&quot;.<br>
<br>
We can do the 18 to book requirement, barely.  We can also do the 12 up there requirement, IF it's a good night for all our folks.  That will be our crapshoot nowadays.  But, then again, if no enchanters show up, and none are available, I declare it FFA too.  We will have less raids then we did.  We will have to work harder to keep them.  But, our lives in Norrath don't revolve around a plane, an epic piece of garbage, or a game.  <br>
<br>
Will some cheat?  Were some cheating before?  To say it wasn't proven doesn't prove it wasn't happening.  Actually, Aldrin mentioned on our Hate raid that a &quot;/who Plane of Hate all&quot; would be a good thing, good idea.  But, realize there is no enforcement possible.  Verant doesn't give a rat's patoot.  It's all about honor, and we can only hope karma applies.<br>
<br>
The Ridgerunners will honor this Summit as we have all of them.  We don't accept WE WANT IT AND WE WANT IT NOW as a valid option for us.  We don't accept &quot;Others cheat so we can&quot; as a valid option for us.  That's for others to do. <br>
<br>
Gregar Mataennoo<br>
Ridgerunner<br>
Ranger 52nd  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uminibaolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MiniBaolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#778899>(10/29/01 2:46:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summit Clarification: Small Guilds</span><hr size=1> The uber zerg guilds SHOULD get a bigger piece of the pie. They have more people. An the reason unguilded get LESS of the pie is because probably 95% of the people 50+ are guilded, and if you make a system where the 5% unguilded people have the advantage, the 95% would be screwed. Not to mention, the guilded people are in power, and they out-number the unguilded, deal with it. Valid concerns are one thing, but whining and complaining and not offering any suggestions that would work isn't very productive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#778899>(10/29/01 5:36:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summit Clarification: Small Guilds</span><hr size=1> Gregar -- RRs have a fine reputation and can probably find a fledgling guild or two that would dual-book with you to get you over your minimums.<br>
<br>
I think what you'll see in the future is that smaller guilds will get more actively involved in alliances.  You'll see posts on Inny.com.  &quot;SmallGuildA looking to form alliance with other small guilds to do planes.&quot;<br>
<br>
I think this is a good thing.  I LOVE the relationship that Unnatural Force formed with Sleeping Giant and Sigils.  It went so well, UF and SG merged to become Horizons.  In doing so, we inherited from the SG folks the relationship with Trade Foundation -- also a great group of people.  And lately, Malus Malorum has been heavily involved in our raids.<br>
<br>
By forcing guilds to dual- (or tri- or quad-) book their raids, I think it'll make the relationships richer for everyone.  Yes, it's more work.  But I do think it'll result in an equitable access to the planes.<br>
<br>
